   <text>
      <body>
         <div>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-1a.1" xml:lang="en">Before the permanent there was no “existence”, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-1a.2" xml:lang="en">it is pure, quite, empty. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-1a.3" xml:lang="en">Purity means ‘great purity’, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-1a.4" xml:lang="en">quiet ‘great quiet’, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-1a.5" xml:lang="en">emptiness ‘great emptiness’. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-1a.6" xml:lang="en">It is satisfied in itself, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-1a.7" xml:lang="en">not hard towards itself; </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-1a.8" xml:lang="en">then “something” arises. </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-2a.1" xml:lang="en">When there is “something” </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-2a.2" xml:lang="en">then there is the pneuma; </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-2a.3" xml:lang="en">when there is the pneuma, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-2a.4" xml:lang="en">there is “existence”, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-2a.5" xml:lang="en">when there is “existence” </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-2a.6" xml:lang="en">there is a beginning; </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-2a.7" xml:lang="en">when there is a beginning, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-2a.8" xml:lang="en">there is a going forth. </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-3a.1" xml:lang="en">When Heaven and Earth do not yet exist, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-3a.2" xml:lang="en">arising and acting are not there (either), </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-3a.3" xml:lang="en">setting out and begetting, emptiness and quiet </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-3a.4" xml:lang="en">are the only things, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-3a.5" xml:lang="en">so solitary, so dim, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-3a.6" xml:lang="en">quiet and unified, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-3a.7" xml:lang="en">and there isn't brightness yet, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-3a.8" xml:lang="en">nor multiplication and begetting. </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-4a.1" xml:lang="en">The pneuma so is spontaneously produced, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-4a.2" xml:lang="en">the permanent in no case produces the pneuma. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-4a.3" xml:lang="en">The pneuma so is spontaneously produced and spontaneously arises. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-4a.4" xml:lang="en">The production of the permanent pneuma is not solitary, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-4a.5" xml:lang="en">there are participants. </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-5a.1" xml:lang="en">‘Something’ is permanent, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-5a.2" xml:lang="en">the one producing ‘something’ is the same. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-5a.3" xml:lang="en">Turbid, restless. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-5a.4" xml:lang="en">Seeking the means of its own production. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-5a.5" xml:lang="en">Opposite produces opposite, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-5a.6" xml:lang="en">similar produces similar, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-5a.7" xml:lang="en">contrarian produces contrarian, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-5a.8" xml:lang="en">negation produces negation, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-5a.9" xml:lang="en">affirmation produces affirmation. </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-6a.1" xml:lang="en">To obtain what one desires one must revert to oneself; </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-6a.2" xml:lang="en">reverting is the living course of action of all living things. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-6a.3" xml:lang="en">The turbid pneuma produces the Earth, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-6a.4" xml:lang="en">the clear pneuma produces Heaven. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-6a.5" xml:lang="en">The pneuma is truly spiritual, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-6a.6" xml:lang="en">everything is so mutually produced, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-6a.7" xml:lang="en">extending and filling Heaven and earth. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-6a.8" xml:lang="en">Their origin is the same but their nature is different, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-6a.9" xml:lang="en">and so they produce what they desire. </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-7a.1" xml:lang="en">Great are Heaven and Earth, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-7a.2" xml:lang="en">mixed and numerous are the many things. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-7a.3" xml:lang="en">At first there was good, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-7a.4" xml:lang="en">there was order and there was no confusion; </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-7a.5" xml:lang="en">since there has been man there has been what is not good, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-7a.6" xml:lang="en">confusion arises from man. </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-8a.1" xml:lang="en">First there is the center, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-8a.2" xml:lang="en">thereupon there is what is external. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-8a.3" xml:lang="en">First there is what is small, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-8a.4" xml:lang="en">thereupon there is what is big. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-8a.5" xml:lang="en">First there is what is soft, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-8a.6" xml:lang="en">thereupon there is what is hard. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-8a.7" xml:lang="en">First there is what is round, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-8a.8" xml:lang="en">thereupon there is what is square. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-8a.9" xml:lang="en">First there is what is obscure, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-8a.10" xml:lang="en">thereupon there is what is bright. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-8a.11" xml:lang="en">First there is what is short, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-8a.12" xml:lang="en">thereupon there is what is long. </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-9a.1" xml:lang="en">After Heaven and Earth have been established, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-9a.2" xml:lang="en">it was through unification that they became as one, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-9a.3" xml:lang="en">it was thorough repetition that they have been returning (?). </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-9a.4" xml:lang="en">The production of permanent pneuma </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-9a.5" xml:lang="en">follows from returning to what they (?) desire; </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-9a.6" xml:lang="en">the bright operations of Heaven, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-9a.7" xml:lang="en">it is only through returning that they are not exhausted. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-9a.8" xml:lang="en">When knowledge is reached the great thoughts are not extinguished. </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-10a.1" xml:lang="en">Existence originates from “something”, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-10a.2" xml:lang="en">nature originates from existence, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-10a.3" xml:lang="en">intention originates from nature, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-10a.4" xml:lang="en">words originate from intention, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-10a.5" xml:lang="en">names originate from words, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-10a.6" xml:lang="en">occupations originate from names. </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-11a.1" xml:lang="en">If “something” is not “something”, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-11a.2" xml:lang="en">it is not called “something.” </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-11a.3" xml:lang="en">If existence is not existence, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-11a.4" xml:lang="en">it is not called existence. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-11a.5" xml:lang="en">If nature is not nature, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-11a.6" xml:lang="en">it is not called nature. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-11a.7" xml:lang="en">If intent is not intent, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-11a.8" xml:lang="en">it is not called intent. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-11a.9" xml:lang="en">If words are not words </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-11a.10" xml:lang="en">they are not called words. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-11a.11" xml:lang="en">If a name is not a name </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-11a.12" xml:lang="en">it is not called a name. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-11a.13" xml:lang="en">If occupations are not occupations </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-11a.14" xml:lang="en">they are not called occupations. </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-12a.1" xml:lang="en">Auspicious righteousness, profitable ability, and the many things (all) originate from (human) work, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-12a.2" xml:lang="en">if there is work thereupon there are operations; </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-12a.3" xml:lang="en">if there is no work there are no operations. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-12a.4" xml:lang="en">All the operations from Heaven arise and act spontaneously, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-12a.5" xml:lang="en">(so) how could operations not be able to continue (indefinitely)? </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-13a.1" xml:lang="en">In every case when speaking a name, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-13a.2" xml:lang="en">even if the first (users) had doubts (about it appropriateness) </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-13a.3" xml:lang="en">if they would speak it with great strength, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-13a.4" xml:lang="en">later (users) would imitate them and follow them in this. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-13a.5" xml:lang="en">All the names under Heaven are empty symbols, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-13a.6" xml:lang="en">they become habits and cannot be changed. </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-14a.1" xml:lang="en">As for all the enterprises under Heaven, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-14a.2" xml:lang="en">(it looks as if) the strong ones bring to fruition the great enterprises under Heaven, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-14a.3" xml:lang="en">(but in fact) they are at loss (?) </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-14a.4" xml:lang="en">and do not act spontaneously, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-14a.5" xml:lang="en">how (otherwise could there be) success or failure, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-14a.6" xml:lang="en">and both could not be discarded. </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-15a.1" xml:lang="en">Every action under Heaven, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-15a.2" xml:lang="en">as long as we do neither reject it </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-15a.3" xml:lang="en">nor join in it, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-15a.4" xml:lang="en">can enact itself. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-15a.5" xml:lang="en">The production of everything under Heaven </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-15a.6" xml:lang="en">(is such that) occupations always revert (to their origin). </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-16a.1" xml:lang="en">Actions under Heaven, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-16a.2" xml:lang="en">(as long as none goes against the extreme (=Dao), </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-16a.3" xml:lang="en">none is not according to its proper place. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-16a.4" xml:lang="en">Every action under Heaven, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-16a.5" xml:lang="en">none does not reach its extreme </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-16a.6" xml:lang="en">and as a result advances. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-16a.7" xml:lang="en">How (can it be said that) something is achieved, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0042_tls_001-16a.8" xml:lang="en">something is lost? </seg>
                </p>

         </div>
      </body>
   </text>
